coot
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:in NZ in fig. or proverbial use for a foolish, clumsy, or bald person as silly as, clumsy as, bald as a coot, or with other depreciatory or contemptuous application to a person of no account
